#   JS-008 [HIGH when wired]: number marshalling precision ‚Äî i64 truncation, NaN/Inf mis-routing, float‚Üíint UB

The convert/rdx number path truncates 64-bit ints through a JS double and
mis-routes NaN/Inf; `POLAddTime((int)ms)` is float‚Üíint UB. Convert path is DEAD
(rdx unwired) ‚Äî fix before wiring. Method: [Issues].

##  Input

### Context
 -  (a) `convert.cpp:97` `JSValueMakeNumber(ctx, top->i)` truncates `i64`
    (`RDX.h:204`) above 2^53 ‚Üí must use BigInt.
 -  (b) `convert.cpp:65-73` number import uses `floor(d)!=d`, which mis-routes NaN
    (‚Üí float branch) and ¬±Inf (‚Üí int branch); must gate on `isfinite` first.
 -  (c) `io.cpp:219-222` `POLAddTime((int)ms)` is float‚Üíint UB for NaN/Inf/negative/
    `>INT_MAX`.
 -  `convert.cpp` is the DEAD rdx path (unwired in `main.cpp:40-42`); `io.cpp:219`
    timer is live. Priority: fix before the rdx path is wired.

### Goals
 -  64-bit ints survive the round trip; NaN/Inf route correctly; the timer rejects
    non-finite / out-of-range delays.

### Constraints
 -  BigInt for 64-bit ints; `isfinite` + explicit range guards before any `(int)`
    cast.

